content.description:
Sit start matching hands on a nice rail, move into a nice crimp then a somewhat big move to a really awesome (and distinctive) jug. Using the arete out right climb to the top.  

  The first three or so moves are money for sure, fun problem.
content.location: Far right on the downhill face. Located on the corner closest to Unknown Boulder B.

content.description: Sit start on a big rail, make one move to the horizontal crack out left then make one somewhat big move to the lip and the mantle top out.
content.location: On the back side from both Witch Doctor and Unknown A-1, right next to the cliff.

content.description:
A really fun problem! Some more powerful climbing down low, then some delicate climbing up high on a beautiful arete.  

  Sit start on a really nice jug, climb out the obvious rail to the lip, then move out onto the face and the wonderful arete. Take the arete to the top.  

  On the right side of the arete, just above the lip there is a nice slanting rail to help.
content.location: Sit start in the back of the roof on the right side (when facing the problem) on a big jug.

content.description: A really nice boulder on the larger side with a handful of problems. Part of the concentrated area where several good sized boulders and a small cliff live.
